CELEBRATED flair bartender, Braide Ifeanyi aka Braidey has been announced the newest ambassador of House of Angostura Nigeria. Braidey joins the pantheon of famous Angostura faces and takes his place among a diverse and accomplished group of renowned bartenders across the world. Speaking in an interview, Braidey said that the decision to join the House of Angostura was based on the heritage and identity of the brand, and the genuine value that the brand adds to the bartending community and Nigeria at large.   Cooking show Sokoyokoto returns     Best Of Nollywood awards: Uzodinma to host 14th Edition     MI Abaga, Chigul, Waje join forces to advocate gender…   Braidey will be taking over the reins from Frank Udeh as the second brand ambassador in Nigeria. Speaking on his deal, Braidey said, “We have always wanted brands to recognise the importance and efforts of bartenders in the wines and spirit industry.” He further said that his position and the initiative would give fellow bartenders hope and rekindle their passion and voice while seeing bartending as a respectable profession.